whereas.text:
Whereas while dating violence, domestic violence, sexual
			 violence, and stalking affect women regardless of age, teens and young women
			 are especially vulnerable;

Whereas being physically and sexually abused leaves teen
			 girls up to 6 times more likely to become pregnant and more than twice as
			 likely to contract a sexually transmitted disease;

Whereas more than 3 times as many tweens (20 percent) as
			 parents of tweens (6 percent) admit that parents know little or nothing about
			 the dating relationships of tweens;

Whereas 74 percent of teenage boys and 66 percent of
			 teenage girls say that they have not had a conversation with a parent about
			 dating abuse in the past year;

Whereas 1 in 4 teens in a relationship say that they have
			 been called names, harassed, or put down by their partner through telephones
			 and texting;

Whereas according to the 2010 College Dating Violence and
			 Abuse Poll by Liz Claiborne Inc., 43 percent of college women who date report
			 experiencing abusive dating behaviors;

Whereas the severity of violence among intimate partners
			 has been shown to be greater in cases where the pattern of violence was
			 established in adolescence;

Whereas educating middle school students and their parents
			 about the importance of building healthy relationships and preventing teen
			 dating violence is key to deterring abuse before it begins;
